---
title: Edge Serialization — HL7v2 to FHIR-like JSON
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant OMIRTH as Orchestrator<br/>Mirth
    participant EDGE as Edge Adapter<br/>(Mirth / Rhino JS)
    participant REGISTRY as OBX Code Registry<br/>(YottaDB)
    participant API as Consumer API
    participant USER as Analyst / Operator

    Note over OMIRTH,USER: Precondition: synthesizer has sent finalized<br/>HL7v2 message to orchestrator Mirth.<br/>Message contains VERDICT OBX row with F status.

    OMIRTH->>OMIRTH: inspect inbound message<br/>detect OBX where code=VERDICT<br/>and result_status=F

    OMIRTH->>EDGE: route to edge adapter channel<br/>MLLP — full HL7v2 finalized message

    EDGE-->>OMIRTH: ACK AA

    EDGE->>REGISTRY: load OBX code registry<br/>^OBX_CODE(*) — all codes, types, display names

    EDGE->>EDGE: parse MSH — extract run_id, timestamp

    EDGE->>EDGE: parse PID — extract claim_id, claim_slug,<br/>claim_description, source_date

    EDGE->>EDGE: parse OBX rows — group by code<br/>apply DetermineOBXResolution per code<br/>(select latest F or C row)

    Note over EDGE: Rhino JS transformer constructs<br/>FHIR-like JSON from resolved OBX rows.<br/>Uses OBX code registry for field name mapping.

    EDGE->>EDGE: construct JSON object<br/>{<br/>  run_id, claim_id, claim_text,<br/>  verdict, confidence_score, narrative,<br/>  coverage: {left, center, right},<br/>  blindspot_score, blindspot_direction,<br/>  claimreview_match, claimreview_verdict,<br/>  domain_evidence_alignment,<br/>  synthesis_signal_count,<br/>  audit_log_ref: "{run_id}.hl7",<br/>  generated_at<br/>}

    EDGE->>EDGE: validate JSON schema<br/>assert required fields present<br/>assert confidence_score in [0.0, 1.0]<br/>assert verdict in controlled vocabulary

    alt schema validation passes
        EDGE->>API: POST /internal/verdicts<br/>Content-Type: application/json<br/>X-Run-Id: RUN-...<br/>{verdict JSON}

        API->>API: persist verdict to verdict store<br/>update run status → PUBLISHED<br/>emit run_complete event

        API-->>EDGE: 201 Created<br/>{verdict_id, published_at}

        Note over API,USER: Verdict is now queryable by consumers.

        USER->>API: GET /verdicts/{verdict_id}
        API-->>USER: 200 OK<br/>{verdict JSON + audit_log_ref}

    else schema validation fails
        EDGE->>EDGE: log validation error<br/>emit AE (Application Error) ACK

        EDGE->>OMIRTH: NACK AE<br/>"Schema validation failed: {field} {reason}"

        Note over OMIRTH: Orchestrator receives AE.<br/>Escalates to run error log.<br/>Does not retry automatically —<br/>schema failure requires investigation.
    end
